Package: artbin
Title: Sample Size and Power for Binary Outcome Clinical Trials
Version: 2.1.2
Authors@R: c(
    person("Abdel", "Babiker", role = "aut"),
    person("Ella", "Marley-Zagar", role = "aut"),
    person("Ian", "White", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "ian.white@ucl.ac.uk"),
    person("Patrick", "Royston", role = "ctb"),
    person("Friederike", "Barthel", role = "ctb"))
Description: Calculates the power or total sample size for randomized clinical
    trials with binary outcomes. Supports superiority, non-inferiority, and
    substantial-superiority designs with two or more arms. Implements the score
    test, Wald test, conditional test (Peto's odds-ratio approximation), and
    linear trend test. Three methods for estimating the null-hypothesis variance
    are available: sample estimates, fixed marginal totals, and constrained
    maximum likelihood. Additional features include allocation ratios, loss to
    follow-up, continuity correction, and local vs distant alternatives.
    Translated from the Stata artbin package (Marley-Zagar et al., 2023,
    <doi:10.1177/1536867X231162026>).
Author: Abdel Babiker [aut], Ella Marley-Zagar [aut], Ian White [aut, cre],
    Patrick Royston [ctb], Friederike Barthel [ctb]
